### 2.5 Django Views & URLs

**Location:** [views.py](file:///home/edelweiss/Program/pythonProject/TATrendingTopic/backend/api/views.py) (441 lines) · [urls.py](file:///home/edelweiss/Program/pythonProject/TATrendingTopic/backend/api/urls.py)

#### Pipeline State Management

Uses an in-memory `_pipeline_state` dict (suitable for development). For production, migrate to Redis/Celery.

```python
_pipeline_state = {
    'status': 'idle',       # idle | running | completed | error
    'df_raw': None,         # Lazy-loaded from perang_iran.csv
    'df_cleaned': None,     # Lazy-loaded from cleaned_output.csv
    'ngrams': None,         # DataFrame from Step 2
    'edge_list': None,      # DataFrame from Step 2
    'burst_analysis': None, # Dict from Step 3
    'network_data': None,   # Dict from Step 4
    'trends': None,         # List from Step 5
    'overview': None,       # Dict from Step 1
}
```

#### Authentication

All endpoints require `X-Api-Key` header, validated by the `@api_key_required` decorator in `auth.py`.

